Despite some impressive world-map graphics and extremely catchy anime-style music, Digimon World 3 disappoints in countless ways.

The game would perhaps be visually palatable if not for the substandard frame rate, but alas, it's a little too jerky to really be pleasing.
The game play and story are very forgettable, and the games brightest point, the multi player, won't shine enough to make this a must have game.

To the game's credit are the tracks: They're well designed, and they get progressively harder as you reach higher levels.
